Seleninum Class 02

All web application are developed using Html.

HTML===>

tags:

<html>
    <body>
        <button> hello </button>
    </body>
</html>


-----------------anchor tag------------------
<a> --> anchor tag
usually the links are placed in this tag, if there is a text in the <a> tag then you can
use linktext locator

---------NOSUCH element exception-------------------
occurs when the driver is unable to find the element on the page
1.the locator is wrong
2.the element is not on that page.

--------------Duplicate Values of attributes------------

<input id="box", name="Username"/> --> Username Box
<input id="box", class="password"/> --> password Box
driver.findElement(By.id("box")).sendKeys("hello");

driver is goinng to go in the DOM from top to bottom, the first tag with id box will
be picked and keys will be sent to that.

